        <bioghist>
            <head>Historical Note</head>

            <p>Founded 1893 by Richard Sears and Alva Roebuck as a mail order business. Sears opened
                its first department stores in 1925 and rose to become the largest retailer in the
                United States. Acquired by KMart in 2005.</p>

            <!-- Use Chronlist Tags clip here for Chronology -->

        </bioghist>
        <!-- Use "Scopecontent Start" clip here for scope/content info. Col. Lev, and arrangement information. -->
        <scopecontent>
            <head>Collection Overview</head>

            <p>Collection consists of seasonal catalogs and wish books spanning the years 1910-1994.
                Catalogs featured the full range of items sold by Sears, from clothing to appliances
                and toys, and served as a bridge between the company's walk-in department stored and
                direct marketing mail order business. Initially featured unbranded products before
                adopting a number of Sears' house brands and eventually featuring nationally branded
                products. </p>

            <!-- OPTIONAL: Use Arrangement clip here for Collection Arrangement section -->

        </scopecontent>
